summary: Okay but Jonah's storyline was so powerful. He literally lied to his friends about not being hungry because he couldn't afford...
body: Okay but Jonah’s storyline was so powerful. He literally lied to his friends about not being hungry because he couldn’t afford it. And when Amber gave him the plate he dug in like he hadn’t eaten in a while. Him only wanting to go to Adrenaline City when he found out he wouldn’t have to pay? A mood. Growing up poor stuff like this has always happened to me. I’ve never experienced bankruptcy cause we’ve never had money to spend and my mom isn’t allowed a credit card. But Jonah? As the poor kid rep I need? I’m down for that.
